{"meta":{"updateDate":1755117017717,"pPcc":"SAT#H","questionId":"7fac16fb","skill_cd":"H.B.","score_band_range_cd":3,"skill_desc":"Linear functions","createDate":1755117017717,"program":"SAT","primary_class_cd_desc":"Algebra","ibn":"","external_id":"3e4d926d-83f1-4d65-87c3-c5889ee7bfa4","primary_class_cd":"H","uId":"162736f0-68ce-40b9-8640-126482e83438","difficulty":"E"},"source":"modern","detail":{"type":"spr","stem":"<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The function <math alttext=\"f\"><mi>f</mi>\n</math> is defined by&nbsp;<math alttext=\"f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals seven tenths x plus 55\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>7</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>55</mn></math>. What is the value of&nbsp;<math alttext=\"f left parenthesis 20 right parenthesis\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mn>20</mn></mfenced></math>?</p>","keys":["69"],"rationale":"<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The correct answer is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"69\"><mn>69</mn></math>. The value of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f left parenthesis 20 right parenthesis\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>)</mo></math> can be found by evaluating the function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f left parenthesis x right parenthesis equals seven tenths x plus 55\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>7</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>55</mn></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x equals 20\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn></math>. Substituting&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"20\"><mn>20</mn></math> for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi></math> in this function yields <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f left parenthesis 20 right parenthesis equals seven tenths left parenthesis 20 right parenthesis plus 55\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>7</mn><mn>10</mn></mfrac><mo>(</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>55</mn></math>, or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f left parenthesis 20 right parenthesis equals 69\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>69</mn></math>. Therefore, the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"f left parenthesis 20 right parenthesis\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>)</mo></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"69\"><mn>69</mn></math>.</p>","externalid":"3e4d926d-83f1-4d65-87c3-c5889ee7bfa4","correct_answer":["69"]}}